title: Carbon fiber composite electrodes derived from metal organic polyhedra-18 and matrimid for hybrid supercapacitors
content:
Energy Adv., 2024, 3,883-893
DOI: 10.1039/D3YA00537B, Paper
Open Access
  This article is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 3.0 Unported Licence.
Syed Fahad Bin Haque, Yafen Tian, Daniel W. Tague, Kenneth J. Balkus, John P. Ferraris
Matrimid and metal–organic polyhedra-18 (MOP-18) electrospun composite nanofibers were utilized to fabricate free-standing, electrically conducting, and high-energy density hybrid supercapacitor electrodes.
